The 2019 amendment,
      effective January 1, 2020, added a colon at the end of paragraph (d)(1);
   added the division (d)(1)(A)(i) designation; substituted "A classroom or online driver training course licensed by the department and which includes a minimum of 30 class hours of instruction; and" for "a driver training course which includes a minimum of 30 class hours of instruction and six hours of private in-car training" in division (d)(1)(A)(i); added division (d)(1)(A)(ii) and subparagraph (d)(1)(B); designated the former last sentence of paragraph (d)(1) as paragraph (d)(2); and redesignated former paragraph (d)(2) as present paragraph (d)(3).
